title: For Sale:  Ruger LCP .380 Auto Pocket Pistol LNIB
postcontent: NRA Condition: Factory New  (unfired)    Specs:    Capacity: 6+1    Slide Material: Alloy Steel    Barrel Material: Alloy Steel    Barrel Length: 2.75"    Grip Frame: Black, High-Performance, Glass-Filled Nylon    Slide Finish: Blued    Barrel Finish: Blued    Width: 0.82"    Sights: Integral    Weight: 9.6 oz.    Feature: Standard Model    Overall: Length 5.16"    Height: 3.60"    Grooves: 6    Twist: 1:16" RH    CA Approved :No    MA Approved & Certified: NoThe ultimate miniature/pocket pistol and offers tremendous utility, especially for the price.  All the miniature .380 (including LCP II) want to add more features and more price but I thought this one captured a nice spot by bringing a trusted brand, low price, impressive utility.  It's just so silly small in my hand that it will always be a chore to use (I've fired them, just not this one), and is frankly the most unpleasant to fire handgun I've ever used, sort of like a fire cracker going off in my one hand contorting itself into some shooting form that neither God nor Weaver ever concieved with one finger on the grip and one one the trigger.  I love firing full sized .45 and .44 mag, but I guess it all comes down to fit and technique and anything that would make it fit me will ruin it's utility (at least as I see it's utility for me).  This is unfired and includes the whole (what I believe is later) retail package that swaps the soft case for a pocket holster.  Also includes 2 magazine floor plates, 1 flat for smallest size, 1 finger extension to help get an extra finger on the grip (hurts pocket drawability for me in many clothes though), black chain lock, manual, etc.I have high praise for the utility and concept but after 2 tries at owning one, I guess I don't need that much utility at the cost of such a poor fit for me.  But if you do want the utility and/or it fits you or you don't mind adding a grip sleeve or whatever to make it fit you, then this is a tremendous value I think.  I'd caution anyone who hasn't tried them that even if it fits your hands it will likely present more percieved recoil than you might expect from .380 because there is simply so little weight or extension to the pistol.  But you don't get such incredible utility without some tradeoffs and there are grip options that help tame it too.All sales and transfers must be done legally.  Please research and ask questions if you don't already know the relevant legal requirements.
